# co-scientist — Scientific Paper Writing Harness

You are a scientific paper writing assistant powered by Claude Code. This
project is a fork of the co-scientist harness, rebuilt on Firebase (Firestore
+ Cloud Storage + Hosting + Auth).

## Where things live

- **All paper metadata** (papers, sections, figures, tables, references,
  reviews, analyses, runs, servers) — Firestore, accessed via the
  `mcp__co_scientist__*` tools.
- **Manuscript content** — `manuscript.md` blob in Cloud Storage,
  regenerated automatically whenever you update a section.
- **Figure images, analysis outputs** — Cloud Storage blobs.
- **Heavy compute** — runs on YOUR machine (`launch_local_job`) or YOUR
  registered HPC (`submit_remote_job`). Never on a cloud server.

## IMPORTANT: Skill Restriction

**ONLY use the skills listed below.** Other skills may appear in `/` from
your user-level config but they are not part of this harness.

## Available Skills

**Writing:**
- `/paper-writing [topic] [journal]` — create or update manuscript sections
- `/paper-revision [paper_slug]` — address open user comments from the dashboard

**Review:**
- `/paper-review [paper_slug]` — run AI reviewers, save to DB

**Export:**
- `/paper-export [paper_slug] docx|tex|pdf` — pandoc-based export, uploads to Storage

**Analysis:**
- `/analysis-run [paper_slug] [analysis] [command]` — local or registered-HPC

**Literature:**
- `/literature-review [topic]` — search PubMed/Crossref, add references

**Images:**
- `/scientific-image [prompt] [figure_number?]` — generate a figure via the
  configured ImageGenerator (subscription-routed if you have one, local Gemini
  otherwise)

## The Comment Loop

Your collaborator (the human) reads the dashboard at the Firebase Hosting URL.
They leave comments — those land in Firestore as reviews with `source='user'`.

When you start a session, the banner tells you how many open user comments
exist. Run `/paper-revision` to walk through and address them. Every
`update_review(..., status='accepted', response='...')` shows up in the
dashboard immediately (Firestore listeners).

## Remote Job Rule (Hard Block)

**Never** launch a long-running remote job via raw `ssh <alias> "nohup ..."`.
The PreToolUse hook will block it.

**Use `mcp__co_scientist__submit_remote_job(...)` instead.** Politeness checks
(load avg, polite-cap) are enforced. Override (for setup commands like
`mkdir`, `conda env create`) by prefixing the command with `# setup` or
including `# allow-untracked` in it.

## Citation Format

Use inline DOI format: `{doi:10.1234/example}`.
References are auto-managed in Firestore; `prepare_export` builds the BibTeX.

## Math Mode

Use `$...$` (inline) or `$$...$$` (display) for variables with sub/superscripts,
Greek letters as variables, fractions, sums. Leave simple equalities like
`n = 69`, `q < 0.005`, `α-helix` (label) as plain text. `prepare_export`
returns `math_warnings` flagging violations.
